            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "Considering #18282, I think there are two options here:\n1. Add a single new extmark flag to control both whether virtual lines scroll horizontally and whether virtual lines wrap.\n   - With `'wrap'`, the flag enables wrapping for virtual lines attached to the extmark.\n   - With `'nowrap'`, the flag doesn't enable wrapping, and instead enables horizontal scrolling for virtual lines.\n2. Use two different extmark flags to control whether virtual lines scroll horizontally and whether virtual lines wrap.\n   - A new value may be added to `virt_lines_leftcol` that enables virtual lines to scroll horizontally.\n   - A new flag controls whether virtual lines wrap, which may even allow wrapping behavior independent of the `'wrap'` option (e.g. with three values `no`, `yes` and `followwrap`).",
