        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> No to scroll is also awkward for inline diffs and copilot ghost text, that's seems like main use case for virtual lines.\n\nWhy is not scrolling horizontally awkward for copilot ghost text? That's the first example I can think of where scrolling horizontally is not desired.",
